========================================================================
BUGS FIXED IN THIS SESSION (9 files changed, +333/-119)
========================================================================

1. PIO TYPE MISMATCH [CRITICAL — fixed all 171 MPAS remap issues]
   pio_initdecomp(PIO_REAL) + pio_write_darray(real(r8)) garbled output.
   Fix: convert to real(4) before write.
   Files: mpas_ocn_fme_horiz_remap.F, mpas_seaice_fme_horiz_remap.F

2. FILL-VALUE ARCHITECTURE [apply_masked — proper masked remapping]
   Old: zeroed fills + frac_b normalization → diluted coastal values, 0 over land.
   New: pack validity mask as extra level, normalize by valid_frac.
   SHR_FILL_VALUE = 1e20 (shared constant, no magic numbers).
   Files: shr_horiz_remap_mod.F90, horiz_remap_mod.F90,
          mpas_ocn_fme_horiz_remap.F, mpas_seaice_fme_horiz_remap.F

3. SOURCE-SIDE FILL VALUES [set fill at point of computation]
   MPAS-SI: iceThicknessMean, surfaceTemperatureMean, airStress → fillValue
            for ice-free cells (was 0.0).
   MPAS-O derived: sst, sss, surfaceHeatFluxTotal → fillValue for land.
   MPAS-O vertical reduce: OHC, FWC, KE → fillValue for land.
   Files: mpas_seaice_fme_derived_fields.F, mpas_ocn_fme_derived_fields.F,
          mpas_ocn_fme_vertical_reduce.F

4. VCOARSEN ARRAY STRIDE MISMATCH [root cause of EAM T_1..T_8 artifacts]
   shr_vcoarsen_avg_cols declares field(ncol,nlev) but receives
   src_field(pcols,pver). When ncol<pcols (14 vs 15), level k>1
   reads padding columns from the previous level. Produces ~95K
   temperatures (should be ~218K) at ~8% of columns.
   Fix: pass src_field(1:ncol,:) to force contiguous copy.
   File: eam_vcoarsen.F90

5. REGISTER_VAR DUPLICATE [PIO def_var "name in use"]
   MPAS framework calls init twice. register_var now skips duplicates.
   Files: mpas_ocn_fme_horiz_remap.F, mpas_seaice_fme_horiz_remap.F

6. VERIFY SCRIPT IMPROVEMENTS
   - tripcolor with antimeridian mask (was scatter, had dateline artifact)
   - Subsampled to 50K points (was hanging on 465K)
   - Side-by-side native vs remapped comparisons
   - Multi-panel T_1..T_8, Q_1..Q_8 layer views
   - Zonal mean profiles, lightbox in HTML
   - Auto-detect depth levels (was hardcoded N_OCN_LAYERS=19)
   - Fixed range checks (surfaceTemperatureMean is degC not K, etc.)
   - ds.sizes instead of ds.dims (suppressed FutureWarning)

